quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
62,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth extols the glory of Allah, the Sovereign, the Holy, the All- Mighty, the All-Wise. {1}",footnotes:1:For explanation
62,2,"He it is Who has sent to the gentiles a Messenger from among themselves, {1} one who rehearses to them His verses, purifies their lives, and imparts to them the Book and the Wisdom {2} although before that they were in utter error; {3}",footnotes:1:Here the word ummi (gentile) has been used as a Jewish term and there is a subtlety in it. The verse means: The All- Mighty and All-Wise Allah has raised a Messenger (peace be upon him) among the Arabs whom the Jews contemptuously consider the gentiles and much below themselves
62,3,"and (He has also) sent him to those others who have not yet joined them. {1} He is the Most Mighty, the Most Wise. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
62,4,"Such is Allah's favour: He bestows it on whomsoever He pleases. Allah is the Lord of abounding favour."
62,5,"The parable of those who were charged with the Torah and then they failed to live up to it {1} is that of a donkey {2} laden with books. Even more evil is the parable of the people who gave the lie to the Signs of Allah. {3} Allah does not direct such wrong-doers to the Right Way.",footnotes:1:That is
62,6,"Tell them: “O you who have become Judaised, {1} if you arrogantly fancy that you are Allah's favourites {2} to the exclusion of all people, then wish for death, if you are truthful in your claim.” {3}",footnotes:1:At several places in the Quran
62,7,"But they shall never wish for death because of the (evil) deeds they have committed. {1} Allah is well aware of these evil-doers.",footnotes:1:In other words
62,8,"Tell them: “The death from which you flee will certainly overtake you. Then you will be returned to Him Who fully knows what is hidden and what is manifest. Thereupon He will let you know all that you used to do.”"
